The former governor of Borno State, Senator Ali Modu Sheriff, has called on the Nasarawa State government to hasten to completion of the ongoing work at the Lafia cargo airport in Lafia, stressing that if completed; the facility would attract investors into the state. Senator Sheriff made this known in a chat with newsmen shortly after paying a congratulatory visit on the Nasarawa State governor, Engineer Abdullahi Sule at the Lafia Government House. The former lawmaker and business mogul said there was need for the state government to complete the airport stage. He added that he felt it was necessary to come and congratulate Engineer Sule, on his assumption of office as governor, saying he was so far impressed with the level of development in the state. “I have not congratulated him formally since he became a governor and I felt it is absolutely necessary to come to the state and congratulate him and to see what he is doing. “And I am quite impressed with the developmental steps that he is taking in the state. I am really impressed,” Sen. Sheriff said. He was optimistic that when the Lafia airport is completed, the sky would be the limit for the state, as according to him, Nasarawa would be in a position to compete with oil producing states. “By the special grace of God, if this airport is completed, the sky will be the limit for Nasarawa State. Very soon, Nasarawa will be competing with those producing oil because natural resources is better than any oil,” he stated. On his part, the governor thanked Senator Sheriff for the visit, saying such visit would smoothen the existing relationship between the two states. Before returning to Abuja, Senator sheriff undertook an inspection tour of the Lafia cargo airport.